[1]
Date: Wed 15 May 2002
From: Carol Lawrence RN BSN <Nitengail8@aol.com>

Re: Hepatitis A Virus IgM Antibody Prevalence
---------------------------------------------
I am a Nurse Epidemiologist who has been doing Hepatitis A virus IgM and
IgG tests as part of occupational exposures for the past 16 years. I have
never seen Hepatitis A virus IgM positives except in individuals who could
document the illness.

--
Carol Lawrence RN BSN
<Nitengail8@aol.com>

