[5]
Date: Thu 16 May 2002
From: Nick Beeching <Nbeeching@aol.com>

Re: Hepatitis A Virus IgM Antibody Prevalence
---------------------------------------------
I am sending this comment without recourse to specific literature, but I
would expect false positive hepatitis A virus IgM antibody rates to be less
than 2 percent at the most. In routine clinical practice we screen many
patients for acute hepatitis A, and false positives are occasionally found
(not 1 in 10), usually in people with positive rheumatoid factor tests. I
am sure you will receive more informed comment on the performance of
different kits from laboratory based colleagues.

--
Dr NJ Beeching
Clinical Lead
Tropical and Infectious Disease Unit
